The leadership of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) has released the list of 24 candidates that have been cleared to contest the 2019 governorship elections. According to the party’s spokesperson, Yekini Nabena, this followed the Governorship Primaries of the All Progressives Congress (APC) held across the country. He said the Party’s National Working Committee (NWC) at its meeting held on Thursday, 4th October, 2018 ratified the reports of the various Electoral Committees and adopts the under-listed as Governorship candidates of the APC for the forthcoming 2019 general elections. Below are the candidates and their respective states:    